        "subject": "LU-19828 kfilnd: Map intf to cxi device kfi config",
        "message": "LU-19828 kfilnd: Map intf to cxi device kfi config\n\nIntroduce lustre_lnet_kfi_intf2cxi() to perform a lookup of the cxi\ndevice based on the provided interface name. This is called by\nlustre_lnet_kfi_intf2nid() to resolve the interface names in the\nYAML configuration path, as well as by jt_add_ni()/jt_del_ni() to\nresolve names on the lnetctl net add/del path.\n\nThis allows administrators to specify regular Linux network device\nnames when configuring kfi networks.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nHPE-bug-id: LUS-10728\nSigned-off-by: Chris Horn <chris.horn@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: I4bfeca9b5fe3bb54ae3c79d46416d24456f33ae4\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/63583\nReviewed-by: Alexander Boyko <alexander.boyko@hpe.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Shaun Tancheff <shaun.tancheff@hpe.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
